sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant Caller
  participant OwnerA as Actor owner epoch N
  participant Cell as Cell persistence facade
  participant Authority as Durable actor authority
  participant OwnerB as Successor owner epoch N+1

  Caller->>OwnerA: actor task mutation
  OwnerA->>Cell: commit candidate state, expected version and epoch N
  Cell->>Authority: literal idempotent mutation operation
  alt Exact receipt returns
    Authority-->>Cell: committed state version V+1
    Cell-->>OwnerA: durable receipt
    OwnerA-->>Caller: mutation result
  else Connection lost after possible commit
    Cell-->>OwnerA: outcome uncertain, never false success
    Cell->>Authority: resolve exact mutation identity
    Authority-->>Cell: committed receipt or not-committed result
    Cell-->>OwnerA: resolved outcome
  end
  Note over OwnerA,Authority: Local candidate state is never authoritative before the durable receipt.
  OwnerA--xCell: owner process or Cell generation is lost
  Authority->>OwnerB: assign epoch N+1 after fenced owner loss
  OwnerB->>Authority: hydrate committed state and version
  Authority-->>OwnerB: state V+1 and current assignment
  OwnerA--xAuthority: stale epoch N commit rejected
  Caller->>OwnerB: next mutation
  OwnerB->>Authority: commit under epoch N+1 and expected version V+1
  Authority-->>OwnerB: durable state version V+2
  OwnerB-->>Caller: continued mutation result
